1
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:55,000
"Lost To You"

2
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:57,700
(Episode 4)

3
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:02,199
We run towards the light

4
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:05,199
but we see the shadows behind us

5
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:08,200
growing longer and longer.

6
00:01:12,666 --> 00:01:13,666
Xu Yuan.

7
00:01:13,750 --> 00:01:14,750
That guy...

8
00:01:14,875 --> 00:01:16,791
Aside from being a total jinx,

9
00:01:17,083 --> 00:01:18,483
he's actually a pretty good person.

10
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:22,833
He's good-tempered,

11
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:24,291
gets good grades,

12
00:01:24,375 --> 00:01:26,055
and I've never seen him get mad at anyone.

13
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:28,553
It's not that we intentionally exclude him.

14
00:01:28,708 --> 00:01:29,458
It's just that he...

15
00:01:29,708 --> 00:01:31,268
never tries to hang out with us either.

16
00:01:33,125 --> 00:01:34,934
When the teacher said to
make a class group chat,

17
00:01:34,958 --> 00:01:36,158
he said he didn't have WeChat.

18
00:01:36,416 --> 00:01:37,434
It's not that he doesn't have WeChat.

19
00:01:37,458 --> 00:01:38,666
He doesn't even have a phone.

20
00:01:39,250 --> 00:01:40,541
No phone at all.

21
00:01:41,833 --> 00:01:43,500
We all think that's pretty weird.

22
00:01:43,833 --> 00:01:44,833
Yeah.

23
00:01:48,583 --> 00:01:50,125
He sounds like an old man.

24
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:10,333
Look who it is.

25
00:02:10,625 --> 00:02:11,625
What's wrong?

26
00:02:12,750 --> 00:02:13,750
Stomachache.

27
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,320
You're a pretty convincing actor.

28
00:02:15,708 --> 00:02:16,708
Spit it out.

29
00:02:16,791 --> 00:02:17,791
What is it?

30
00:02:18,125 --> 00:02:19,325
How did you know I was faking?

31
00:02:19,583 --> 00:02:21,223
You've been like this since we were kids.

32
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:22,250
Whenever you lie,

33
00:02:22,541 --> 00:02:23,541
you touch your ear.

34
00:02:27,125 --> 00:02:28,416
I just wanted to ask...

35
00:02:28,666 --> 00:02:29,666
about Xu Yuan.

36
00:02:30,500 --> 00:02:32,060
Why the sudden interest in a classmate?

37
00:02:33,250 --> 00:02:34,250
I'm curious.

38
00:02:35,041 --> 00:02:36,041
He's my deskmate.

39
00:02:36,166 --> 00:02:37,206
If I don't understand him,

40
00:02:38,333 --> 00:02:39,453
I can't focus on my studies.

41
00:02:42,666 --> 00:02:43,666
Fine.

42
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,083
His family situation...

43
00:02:45,625 --> 00:02:46,705
I don't know much about it.

44
00:02:47,291 --> 00:02:48,291
But there is someone...

45
00:02:48,708 --> 00:02:49,708
who might know.

46
00:02:50,916 --> 00:02:51,916
Who?

47
00:02:52,791 --> 00:02:53,791
Bian Ye.

48
00:02:55,458 --> 00:02:56,458
Bian Ye?

49
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:00,333
You mean that kid with the red hair?

50
00:03:00,708 --> 00:03:01,892
The one who's always fighting?

51
00:03:01,916 --> 00:03:02,916
Yeah.

52
00:03:02,958 --> 00:03:04,838
He helps out at Xu Yuan's
mother's noodle shop.

53
00:03:05,458 --> 00:03:06,458
He should know a lot.

54
00:03:06,541 --> 00:03:08,000
If you want to know about Xu Yuan,

55
00:03:08,625 --> 00:03:09,705
you could probably ask him.

56
00:03:12,083 --> 00:03:14,083
You seem to know a lot about Bian Ye.

57
00:03:14,666 --> 00:03:15,666
Are you close with him?

58
00:03:19,791 --> 00:03:20,791
I'm tutoring him.

59
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:23,750
In exchange, he has to stop
hanging out with that crowd.

60
00:03:27,291 --> 00:03:28,375
Why are you so nice to him?

61
00:03:32,208 --> 00:03:33,208
Wang-wang.

62
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,000
Some things...

63
00:03:35,625 --> 00:03:36,708
don't need so many reasons.

64
00:03:38,625 --> 00:03:40,305
Being good to the people you care about...

65
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:41,953
is nothing to be ashamed of.

66
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,040
Whether they're friends...

67
00:03:45,083 --> 00:03:46,083
or something else.

68
00:03:47,250 --> 00:03:48,250
Just like you...

69
00:03:50,083 --> 00:03:51,563
you seem to care a lot about Xu Yuan.

70
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:02,750
Trying to bribe me?

71
00:04:03,166 --> 00:04:04,166
I don't smoke.

72
00:04:05,041 --> 00:04:06,241
You want to ask about Xu Yuan.

73
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:10,250
His family...

74
00:04:12,708 --> 00:04:13,166
is dirt poor.

75
00:04:13,416 --> 00:04:14,536
A little better off than me,

76
00:04:14,583 --> 00:04:15,583
but not by much.

77
00:04:16,375 --> 00:04:18,250
Auntie Meixi doesn't make much in a month.

78
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:20,158
And she has to raise two kids.

79
00:04:24,041 --> 00:04:25,721
Then why are you the only one helping out?

80
00:04:25,791 --> 00:04:26,791
Why doesn't he?

81
00:04:27,541 --> 00:04:28,625
With his jinx-like nature,

82
00:04:28,750 --> 00:04:30,030
who would dare get close to him?

83
00:04:30,291 --> 00:04:31,809
The most he can do is run
some deliveries for his mom.

84
00:04:31,833 --> 00:04:32,833
And I mean literally run.

85
00:04:35,791 --> 00:04:36,831
Making deliveries on foot?

86
00:04:37,291 --> 00:04:37,875
What was he thinking?

87
00:04:38,166 --> 00:04:39,166
It's hilarious.

88
00:04:39,250 --> 00:04:40,850
Who makes deliveries on foot these days?

89
00:04:41,333 --> 00:04:43,013
I've set him up with a few part-time jobs,

90
00:04:43,541 --> 00:04:45,541
but they all bailed when
they heard he was a jinx.

91
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:48,059
Now, the most he can do
is move cargo at the docks

92
00:04:48,083 --> 00:04:49,434
or help people mend their fishing nets.

93
00:04:49,458 --> 00:04:51,138
But he's been really short on cash lately.

94
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:53,036
I think it's for his sister.

95
00:04:56,916 --> 00:04:57,375
Xu Yuan.

96
00:04:57,875 --> 00:04:59,755
There's a shipment of
glass to unload tomorrow.

97
00:05:00,166 --> 00:05:01,726
It's a bit dangerous, but it pays well.

98
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:02,791
Fifty. You in?

99
00:05:02,916 --> 00:05:03,333
I'm in.

100
00:05:03,708 --> 00:05:04,125
What time?

101
00:05:04,625 --> 00:05:05,785
Same time as always tomorrow.

102
00:05:06,083 --> 00:05:06,583
But...

103
00:05:06,916 --> 00:05:07,958
let's be clear.

104
00:05:08,458 --> 00:05:09,892
If you break the glass, you pay for it.

105
00:05:09,916 --> 00:05:10,916
Okay.

106
00:05:11,125 --> 00:05:12,125
Here.

107
00:05:14,083 --> 00:05:15,083
Thanks, Uncle.

108
00:05:29,041 --> 00:05:29,458
Look!

109
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,059
Isn't that Zhan Wang from
the high school division?

110
00:05:31,083 --> 00:05:32,208
He's so handsome.

111
00:05:32,333 --> 00:05:33,000
It really is him.

112
00:05:33,125 --> 00:05:35,125
What's he doing over in
the middle school section?

113
00:05:35,541 --> 00:05:36,541
See that?

114
00:05:36,583 --> 00:05:38,000
That's my brother's friend.

115
00:05:38,208 --> 00:05:39,208
He's here to see me.

116
00:05:39,708 --> 00:05:41,333
Brother Zhan Wang, I'm over here!

117
00:05:47,125 --> 00:05:48,125
Taro boba tea.

118
00:05:48,416 --> 00:05:48,875
Half sugar.

119
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:50,333
Thanks, big brother.

120
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:51,791
Brother Zhan Wang is the best.

121
00:05:53,125 --> 00:05:54,125
What did you need me for?

122
00:05:55,083 --> 00:05:56,625
Are you here to ask about my brother?

123
00:05:58,250 --> 00:05:59,250
Just a quick question.

124
00:06:01,666 --> 00:06:02,666
Your brother is so old,

125
00:06:03,625 --> 00:06:05,416
why doesn't he have a phone?

126
00:06:05,875 --> 00:06:07,166
Well...

127
00:06:08,083 --> 00:06:09,083
My brother...

128
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,666
he doesn't talk much.

129
00:06:11,125 --> 00:06:12,765
I'm always the one pestering him to talk.

130
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,708
And when we communicate at home,

131
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:16,208
we just write notes to each other.

132
00:06:17,958 --> 00:06:19,000
Actually, I think...

133
00:06:19,666 --> 00:06:21,833
he just can't bear to spend
money on a new phone,

134
00:06:22,125 --> 00:06:23,541
so he says that on purpose.

135
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:27,833
He's that short on money?

136
00:06:27,958 --> 00:06:30,000
It's kind of embarrassing to say,

137
00:06:31,166 --> 00:06:33,541
but my brother is doing all this...

138
00:06:33,708 --> 00:06:35,041
for me.

139
00:06:35,166 --> 00:06:36,166
For you?

140
00:06:36,875 --> 00:06:38,075
I want to take acting classes,

141
00:06:38,416 --> 00:06:40,500
but the ones in town are too expensive.

142
00:06:40,916 --> 00:06:42,356
One session costs over ten thousand.

143
00:06:42,583 --> 00:06:43,875
After my brother found out,

144
00:06:44,125 --> 00:06:46,000
he secretly took on a bunch of odd jobs.

145
00:06:46,375 --> 00:06:48,083
And he's kind of a dummy.

146
00:06:48,416 --> 00:06:49,434
The last time he was moving glass,

147
00:06:49,458 --> 00:06:50,666
he cut his hand all up.

148
00:06:51,541 --> 00:06:52,666
When I asked him about it,

149
00:06:53,458 --> 00:06:55,250
he just said he fell by accident.

150
00:06:59,250 --> 00:07:00,250
I see.

151
00:07:00,583 --> 00:07:02,333
I'll take care of the acting classes.

152
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:06,500
This is for you.

153
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:09,500
But it's not free.

154
00:07:10,041 --> 00:07:11,934
From now on, if anything
happens with your brother,

155
00:07:11,958 --> 00:07:12,958
you tell me immediately.

156
00:07:13,791 --> 00:07:14,791
Deal.

157
00:07:15,708 --> 00:07:17,750
These three are brand new releases.

158
00:07:18,166 --> 00:07:19,166
Don't worry.

159
00:07:19,250 --> 00:07:20,530
I'll tell you everything I know.

160
00:07:20,708 --> 00:07:22,375
Besides, when it comes to my brother,

161
00:07:22,583 --> 00:07:23,583
I know everything.

162
00:07:23,875 --> 00:07:24,708
Last night,

163
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:26,809
he stayed up late helping
Mom with the account books.

164
00:07:26,833 --> 00:07:28,250
His shoes are getting a little old.

165
00:07:28,625 --> 00:07:29,750
He needs a new pair.

166
00:07:30,375 --> 00:07:31,375
Got it.

167
00:07:31,416 --> 00:07:32,416
I'm heading out.

168
00:07:33,625 --> 00:07:34,625
Bye, Brother Zhan Wang.

169
00:07:40,708 --> 00:07:41,708
Get on.

170
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:43,500
This bike is for you.

171
00:07:44,083 --> 00:07:45,684
Don't you have to make
deliveries for your mom?

172
00:07:45,708 --> 00:07:46,708
Running is too slow.

173
00:07:47,583 --> 00:07:49,503
This bike is fast. You
can make more deliveries.

174
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,000
I don't want it.

175
00:07:53,041 --> 00:07:54,041
It's not a gift.

176
00:07:54,250 --> 00:07:55,250
The condition is...

177
00:07:55,333 --> 00:07:57,500
you have to take me to
and from school every day.

178
00:07:58,291 --> 00:07:59,916
I don't want to walk every day.

179
00:08:00,083 --> 00:08:01,083
It's exhausting.

180
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:02,166
No.

181
00:08:02,583 --> 00:08:04,063
It's dangerous for me to ride a bike.

182
00:08:05,875 --> 00:08:06,875
Just try it.

183
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:09,208
I'm a seasoned veteran.

184
00:08:09,416 --> 00:08:11,500
I'm not afraid of your jinx-like nature.

185
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:13,291
Get on.

186
00:08:29,334 --> 00:08:33,044
[A full dossier of information on Bian Ye]

187
00:08:38,458 --> 00:08:39,958
So, after I check in with you today,

188
00:08:40,291 --> 00:08:41,458
is my debt to you paid off?

189
00:08:41,875 --> 00:08:42,250
Sit.

190
00:08:42,666 --> 00:08:43,666
Let's talk.

191
00:08:44,958 --> 00:08:45,958
About what?

192
00:08:46,166 --> 00:08:47,267
About why you left Jingzhou...

193
00:08:47,291 --> 00:08:48,731
and chose to come back to this dump?

194
00:08:48,875 --> 00:08:50,555
Or should we talk about your rich old man?

195
00:08:55,916 --> 00:08:56,976
Let's talk about your father.

196
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,080
None of your damn business.

197
00:08:59,375 --> 00:09:00,375
Bian Jianguo.

198
00:09:00,583 --> 00:09:01,583
Age 42.

199
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:02,726
Five years ago, at a casino,

200
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,270
he racked up 300,000 in gambling debt.

201
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:05,976
He packed his things in the
middle of the night and ran.

202
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,400
Leaving you and your mother behind.

203
00:09:08,458 --> 00:09:10,218
And a bunch of debt
collectors at your door.

204
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:11,208
Zhan Xu.

205
00:09:11,625 --> 00:09:12,785
You've been investigating me?

206
00:09:12,916 --> 00:09:13,956
What are you trying to do?

207
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:16,375
Come on.

208
00:09:16,791 --> 00:09:17,500
I'm taking you somewhere.

209
00:09:17,708 --> 00:09:18,250
I'm not going.

210
00:09:18,458 --> 00:09:19,476
If you come with me today,

211
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:20,540
your debt will be cleared.

212
00:09:21,125 --> 00:09:22,309
The path you take from here on...

213
00:09:22,333 --> 00:09:23,333
is up to you.

214
00:09:30,541 --> 00:09:31,625
Why did you bring me here?

215
00:09:32,333 --> 00:09:33,333
You'll see.

216
00:09:37,375 --> 00:09:38,375
Limpy Li.

217
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:40,559
Back in the day, he
fought for turf at the docks

218
00:09:40,583 --> 00:09:41,583
and got his leg broken.

219
00:09:42,166 --> 00:09:43,791
Now he gambles every day,

220
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:45,041
and is up to his ears in debt.

221
00:09:45,041 --> 00:09:45,625
When are you ever...

222
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:47,291
going to get a real job?

223
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:49,250
So what if I don't have a job?

224
00:09:49,251 --> 00:09:50,642
Am I just sitting around doing nothing?

225
00:09:50,666 --> 00:09:51,125
Have I ever let you down?

226
00:09:51,125 --> 00:09:52,125
Wang Wei.

227
00:09:53,291 --> 00:09:55,500
He was a notorious thug back in the day.

228
00:09:56,208 --> 00:09:57,208
Brawling,

229
00:09:57,250 --> 00:09:58,330
running protection rackets.

230
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,125
Now he lives off his wife.

231
00:10:00,583 --> 00:10:01,583
He drinks every day,

232
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,400
and beats his wife when he's drunk.

233
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:11,750
Old Zhao the Third.

234
00:10:12,458 --> 00:10:13,938
Used to be the big shot of Hong Town.

235
00:10:14,625 --> 00:10:16,583
Now he picks through trash for a living.

236
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:30,598
What's your point in showing me all this?

237
00:10:30,958 --> 00:10:32,208
To show off how much you know?

238
00:10:32,458 --> 00:10:33,517
Or are you trying to tell me

239
00:10:33,541 --> 00:10:35,041
I'll end up just like these losers?

240
00:10:36,375 --> 00:10:37,375
Bian Ye.

241
00:10:38,875 --> 00:10:39,875
You're a lot like them.

242
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:41,870
You think school is useless.

243
00:10:42,541 --> 00:10:44,221
You think being tough is all that matters.

244
00:10:44,458 --> 00:10:46,101
You think you can just worry about tomorrow

245
00:10:46,125 --> 00:10:47,125
when it comes.

246
00:10:48,041 --> 00:10:49,041
I'm not like them.

247
00:10:49,458 --> 00:10:50,458
How are you different?

248
00:10:51,625 --> 00:10:52,625
Maybe your father

249
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:55,541
said the exact same thing back in his day.

250
00:10:58,916 --> 00:10:59,458
I'm not...

251
00:10:59,916 --> 00:11:00,916
I just...

252
00:11:03,583 --> 00:11:04,583
Just what?

253
00:11:05,541 --> 00:11:06,541
Just occasionally

254
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:08,291
collecting debts for loan sharks.

255
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,875
Just occasionally moving some smuggled
goods.

256
00:11:11,833 --> 00:11:12,833
Bian Ye.

257
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:14,750
With things like this,

258
00:11:15,458 --> 00:11:16,458
if you do it once,

259
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,000
you'll do it ten times.

260
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,220
The stakes will just get higher and higher.

261
00:11:20,541 --> 00:11:22,181
And eventually, you could end up in jail.

262
00:11:22,291 --> 00:11:23,771
Have you ever thought about your mom?

263
00:11:31,750 --> 00:11:33,750
Then tell me what I'm supposed to do.

264
00:11:34,166 --> 00:11:34,958
If I don't do this stuff,

265
00:11:35,125 --> 00:11:36,642
how am I supposed to pay off my debts?

266
00:11:36,666 --> 00:11:38,386
How am I supposed to buy my mom's medicine?

267
00:11:38,708 --> 00:11:39,708
School?

268
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,440
Can school turn into cash overnight?

269
00:11:41,541 --> 00:11:42,541
Make a deal with me.

270
00:11:42,958 --> 00:11:43,958
What are you up to now?

271
00:11:44,125 --> 00:11:45,125
Starting tomorrow,

272
00:11:45,958 --> 00:11:47,278
you report to my place every day.

273
00:11:48,083 --> 00:11:49,208
I'll give you a test.

274
00:11:49,916 --> 00:11:50,916
When you finish,

275
00:11:51,375 --> 00:11:52,375
I'll give you 300.

276
00:11:54,083 --> 00:11:55,083
Are you kidding me?

277
00:11:55,375 --> 00:11:56,375
I'm a man of my word.

278
00:11:58,125 --> 00:11:59,805
If your score is higher than the last one,

279
00:12:00,666 --> 00:12:02,208
I'll give you an extra 500 as a bonus.

280
00:12:03,416 --> 00:12:04,416
That way,

281
00:12:04,708 --> 00:12:06,828
you'll make more than you
do hustling on the streets.

282
00:12:07,291 --> 00:12:08,291
And it's safer.

283
00:12:08,958 --> 00:12:11,198
If you can stick with it until
you graduate high school,

284
00:12:11,458 --> 00:12:13,000
I'll even help you pay for college.

285
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:15,208
You can learn a real trade,

286
00:12:16,041 --> 00:12:17,521
and support yourself and your family.

287
00:12:18,583 --> 00:12:19,291
Don't you want to escape

288
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:20,541
a life like your father's?

289
00:12:22,083 --> 00:12:23,083
This is the first step.

290
00:12:24,750 --> 00:12:25,910
Making money with your brain,

291
00:12:27,750 --> 00:12:28,875
not your fists.

292
00:12:37,625 --> 00:12:38,166
Bian Ye.

293
00:12:38,458 --> 00:12:39,476
I've been looking all over for you.

294
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:40,500
We've got a job tonight.

295
00:12:40,625 --> 00:12:41,625
Let's go.

296
00:12:45,083 --> 00:12:46,083
The choice is yours.

297
00:12:47,416 --> 00:12:49,541
You can keep cowering in the dark,

298
00:12:50,375 --> 00:12:52,041
or you can step into the light.

299
00:12:58,291 --> 00:12:59,291
Bian Ye.

300
00:13:00,250 --> 00:13:02,010
Bian Ye, I've been
looking all over for you.

301
00:13:05,666 --> 00:13:06,666
I'm not going.

302
00:13:19,416 --> 00:13:20,416
300 a day, right?

303
00:13:21,125 --> 00:13:21,458
Right.

304
00:13:21,666 --> 00:13:23,066
And a 500 bonus for a higher score.

305
00:13:23,208 --> 00:13:24,208
Yes.

306
00:13:24,458 --> 00:13:25,458
300 on the first day.

307
00:13:25,541 --> 00:13:26,541
800 on the second.

308
00:13:26,916 --> 00:13:27,916
The third day...

309
00:13:29,291 --> 00:13:30,291
In one month,

310
00:13:30,458 --> 00:13:32,208
that's a total of 23,700 yuan.

311
00:13:35,875 --> 00:13:36,875
What time tomorrow?

312
00:13:37,083 --> 00:13:38,083
And where?

313
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:39,500
After school.

314
00:13:40,250 --> 00:13:41,250
Meet me at the clinic.

315
00:13:46,250 --> 00:13:47,250
See you tomorrow.

316
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:08,583
The doorknob is fixed, too.

317
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:12,708
The yard is all tidied up.

318
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,041
And the swing...

319
00:14:16,125 --> 00:14:17,416
The swing is hung up, too.

320
00:14:17,916 --> 00:14:18,541
Did you do this?

321
00:14:18,791 --> 00:14:19,791
No.

322
00:14:20,166 --> 00:14:21,166
Wasn't it you?

323
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,166
Could it be

324
00:14:25,708 --> 00:14:28,375
we have a secret helper?

325
00:14:32,083 --> 00:14:33,083
New shoes!

326
00:14:37,583 --> 00:14:39,642
I wonder if it's because I
told Zhan Wang yesterday...

327
00:14:39,666 --> 00:14:40,666
and he...

328
00:14:41,041 --> 00:14:42,166
He even got me a pair!

329
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,208
He's so thoughtful.

330
00:14:45,416 --> 00:14:46,583
Bro, let's try them on.

331
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:00,690
Is Xu Yuan wearing the latest model?

332
00:15:00,958 --> 00:15:01,875
Xu Yuan must have struck it rich.

333
00:15:01,958 --> 00:15:03,238
Those shoes are crazy expensive.

334
00:15:04,125 --> 00:15:05,125
Zhan Wang's are too.

335
00:15:05,625 --> 00:15:06,166
Morning.

336
00:15:06,375 --> 00:15:07,375
Morning.

337
00:15:13,708 --> 00:15:14,708
Zhan Wang.

338
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:16,916
Those shoes at my doorstep...

339
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:19,071
You left them there, didn't you?

340
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:21,541
What shoes?

341
00:15:22,166 --> 00:15:23,726
I don't know what you're talking about.

342
00:15:24,083 --> 00:15:25,083
And...

343
00:15:25,333 --> 00:15:26,375
the gate to the yard,

344
00:15:27,208 --> 00:15:28,208
the clothesline,

345
00:15:28,458 --> 00:15:29,458
the faucet holder...

346
00:15:33,583 --> 00:15:34,833
What are you talking about?

347
00:15:35,625 --> 00:15:36,625
I have no idea.

348
00:15:37,916 --> 00:15:39,750
Then maybe someone left them by mistake.

349
00:15:40,333 --> 00:15:42,000
Then I'd better put them away tonight.

350
00:15:42,291 --> 00:15:43,811
The owner might come looking for them.

351
00:15:44,916 --> 00:15:45,916
Wait.

352
00:15:47,916 --> 00:15:48,916
I heard

353
00:15:49,041 --> 00:15:50,166
there's some kind of

354
00:15:51,208 --> 00:15:53,333
community outreach program.

355
00:15:53,625 --> 00:15:56,333
They give supplies to students in need.

356
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:01,000
The community outreach
program gives out this brand?

357
00:16:04,375 --> 00:16:05,875
The brand was having a sale.

358
00:16:06,958 --> 00:16:07,958
A clearance sale.

359
00:16:08,458 --> 00:16:09,458
A clearance sale.

360
00:16:10,375 --> 00:16:11,375
Clearance?

361
00:16:11,666 --> 00:16:14,066
Giving away one pair of men's
shoes and one pair of women's?

362
00:16:14,166 --> 00:16:16,206
And they just happen to
be mine and Xu Nuo's sizes?

363
00:16:23,625 --> 00:16:24,625
Whatever.

364
00:16:25,333 --> 00:16:26,533
Since someone gave them to me,

365
00:16:26,833 --> 00:16:27,873
I might as well wear them.

366
00:16:28,541 --> 00:16:29,621
They're pretty comfortable.

367
00:16:32,125 --> 00:16:33,750
You've got good taste.

368
00:16:57,208 --> 00:16:58,083
I'm done.

369
00:16:58,208 --> 00:16:59,448
These questions are impossible.

370
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:18,190
Your score is higher than last time.

371
00:17:18,541 --> 00:17:19,581
But I still didn't pass.

372
00:17:20,708 --> 00:17:21,708
So no bonus.

373
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:24,083
But you still get the base pay of 300.

374
00:17:30,541 --> 00:17:31,541
Here you go.

375
00:17:33,958 --> 00:17:35,059
Your tooth is bothering you again?

376
00:17:35,083 --> 00:17:36,083
None of your business.

377
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:37,333
I'm a dentist.

378
00:17:38,041 --> 00:17:39,041
Let me take a look.

379
00:17:50,125 --> 00:17:51,125
You have a cavity.

380
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:53,250
It's a pretty deep one.

381
00:17:56,125 --> 00:17:57,565
And it looks like this tooth here...

382
00:17:58,291 --> 00:17:59,291
is cracked.

383
00:18:01,583 --> 00:18:02,208
Is it this one?

384
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:03,500
Ow!

385
00:18:07,458 --> 00:18:08,458
The power's out.

386
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:17,333
The power's out.

387
00:18:17,791 --> 00:18:19,391
Let me just file down the tooth for now.

388
00:18:24,166 --> 00:18:25,166
Okay, open up.

389
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,000
Does it hurt?

390
00:19:11,083 --> 00:19:12,083
All done.

391
00:19:12,833 --> 00:19:14,458
That's all we can do for today.

392
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,353
Remember to come back for a follow-up.

393
00:19:56,958 --> 00:19:58,198
You can't water mint like that.

394
00:19:58,958 --> 00:19:59,958
You'll cause root rot.

395
00:20:02,291 --> 00:20:03,291
I was just passing by.

396
00:20:04,375 --> 00:20:05,375
It looked a little dry.

397
00:20:07,166 --> 00:20:08,606
Just passing by with a full toolbox?

398
00:20:11,291 --> 00:20:12,451
I have to fix Bian Ye's bike.

399
00:20:12,916 --> 00:20:13,458
I'm in a hurry.

400
00:20:13,625 --> 00:20:14,625
I gotta go.

401
00:20:18,125 --> 00:20:19,125
Have you had dinner yet?

402
00:20:19,916 --> 00:20:20,375
Not yet.

403
00:20:20,416 --> 00:20:21,736
My mom made seafood congee today.

404
00:20:21,916 --> 00:20:22,916
Want to join?

405
00:20:29,125 --> 00:20:30,125
Drink it while it's hot.

406
00:20:30,166 --> 00:20:31,206
I made extra congee today.

407
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:33,958
Xu Nuo, time to eat.

408
00:20:34,791 --> 00:20:35,250
Coming.

409
00:20:35,666 --> 00:20:36,166
Thank you, Auntie.

410
00:20:36,166 --> 00:20:37,166
It's nothing.

411
00:20:38,166 --> 00:20:39,166
Zhan Wang, you're here.

412
00:20:39,625 --> 00:20:40,791
You're amazing.

413
00:20:41,208 --> 00:20:41,666
Mom.

414
00:20:41,958 --> 00:20:44,125
Zhan Wang signed me up
for an online acting class.

415
00:20:44,333 --> 00:20:44,916
I looked it up.

416
00:20:45,208 --> 00:20:46,458
The teacher is from Jingzhou.

417
00:20:46,708 --> 00:20:48,108
A professor from the drama academy.

418
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:50,166
He's taught so many big stars.

419
00:20:50,375 --> 00:20:51,958
I'm going to be a big star too.

420
00:20:54,125 --> 00:20:55,125
An acting class?

421
00:20:56,916 --> 00:20:58,125
How much did that cost?

422
00:20:58,750 --> 00:20:59,500
Well, Xiao Wang...

423
00:20:59,750 --> 00:21:00,166
Auntie.

424
00:21:00,625 --> 00:21:01,458
It didn't cost much.

425
00:21:01,583 --> 00:21:01,916
You see,

426
00:21:01,917 --> 00:21:03,837
Professor Li happens to
be a friend of my mom's.

427
00:21:04,291 --> 00:21:06,051
He said he wanted to
take on a few students.

428
00:21:06,416 --> 00:21:07,416
Xu Nuo is talented.

429
00:21:08,916 --> 00:21:11,041
But we can't let you pay for it.

430
00:21:12,541 --> 00:21:13,333
Mom.

431
00:21:13,458 --> 00:21:14,708
Please just let me take it.

432
00:21:15,083 --> 00:21:16,125
Professor Li said...

433
00:21:16,458 --> 00:21:18,098
the first month is just a trial class.

434
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:19,291
If I'm not a good fit,

435
00:21:19,458 --> 00:21:20,916
he won't even accept me.

436
00:21:25,458 --> 00:21:26,166
Xiao Wang.

437
00:21:26,250 --> 00:21:27,875
I don't know how to thank you.

438
00:21:28,041 --> 00:21:29,083
It's nothing, Auntie.

439
00:21:29,458 --> 00:21:30,458
Where's Xu Yuan?

440
00:21:33,166 --> 00:21:33,958
Zhan Wang.

441
00:21:34,125 --> 00:21:34,625
Did you forget?

442
00:21:35,125 --> 00:21:37,875
My brother is the infamous jinx...

443
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:40,708
I'm used to eating alone.

444
00:21:43,791 --> 00:21:44,791
Hurry up and eat.

445
00:21:47,875 --> 00:21:49,075
Did you sneak some extra food?

446
00:21:49,250 --> 00:21:50,250
Let me see.

447
00:21:51,125 --> 00:21:52,125
Come on, eat over there.

448
00:21:52,291 --> 00:21:53,291
No.

449
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:54,500
Come on.

450
00:22:07,500 --> 00:22:09,875
Let me see what's in your bowl.

451
00:22:17,666 --> 00:22:18,666
Look at those two.

452
00:22:20,333 --> 00:22:21,333
Eat up.

453
00:22:25,291 --> 00:22:26,771
You're pretty good at washing dishes.

454
00:22:28,208 --> 00:22:29,688
I've been doing it since I was a kid.

455
00:22:31,666 --> 00:22:32,916
Do you have a phone charger?

456
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:33,541
Can I borrow it for a bit?

457
00:22:33,625 --> 00:22:34,625
My phone is dead.

458
00:22:35,208 --> 00:22:36,208
I don't have a phone.

459
00:22:36,791 --> 00:22:37,791
No phone?

460
00:22:39,041 --> 00:22:40,601
Is your mom usually that strict with you?

461
00:22:40,625 --> 00:22:41,625
I don't need one.

462
00:22:44,166 --> 00:22:45,766
Then how do you contact your classmates?

463
00:22:46,791 --> 00:22:47,791
I don't.

464
00:22:48,958 --> 00:22:49,958
What if you need to?

465
00:22:51,625 --> 00:22:53,425
There's nothing I need
to contact them about.

466
00:22:55,041 --> 00:22:56,121
There's a class group chat.

467
00:22:56,958 --> 00:22:58,158
They post everything in there.

468
00:22:58,333 --> 00:22:59,333
A-Ze tells me.

469
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:01,666
What if A-Ze can't reach you either?

470
00:23:03,416 --> 00:23:04,416
Zhan Wang.

471
00:23:06,458 --> 00:23:07,458
I don't have any friends.

472
00:23:09,416 --> 00:23:10,833
And no one I need to contact.

473
00:23:16,500 --> 00:23:17,860
The most important people to me...

474
00:23:19,250 --> 00:23:20,375
are all in this house.

475
00:23:26,083 --> 00:23:27,083
Does that include me?

476
00:23:37,208 --> 00:23:37,666
Auntie.

477
00:23:38,041 --> 00:23:38,583
Let me help you.

478
00:23:38,875 --> 00:23:39,892
No, it's fine. I can do it.

479
00:23:39,916 --> 00:23:40,541
It's okay, I'll get it.

480
00:23:40,875 --> 00:23:41,166
I'll wipe it.

481
00:23:41,166 --> 00:23:41,583
Don't.

482
00:23:41,583 --> 00:23:42,250
Zhan Wang.

483
00:23:42,583 --> 00:23:44,583
You and my brother are a good match.

484
00:23:45,291 --> 00:23:46,125
Thanks for your help.

485
00:23:46,250 --> 00:23:47,570
Zhan Wang, you can leave it here.

486
00:24:05,427 --> 00:24:07,281
[Lending this, [so you're] easy to reach]

487
00:24:08,666 --> 00:24:09,666
I'm not giving it to you.

488
00:24:10,125 --> 00:24:11,125
I'm lending it.

489
00:24:11,875 --> 00:24:12,875
Why?

490
00:24:17,541 --> 00:24:18,661
I want to add you on WeChat.

491
00:24:19,875 --> 00:24:21,559
Besides, you have to
be my training partner.

492
00:24:21,583 --> 00:24:23,103
I need to be able to find you anytime.

493
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:26,500
Thanks.

494
00:24:29,041 --> 00:24:30,281
Do you know how to use a phone?

495
00:24:34,416 --> 00:24:35,416
Class.

496
00:24:35,708 --> 00:24:38,250
Next month is the all-school sports meet.

497
00:24:38,583 --> 00:24:40,416
This will be our last group activity.

498
00:24:41,041 --> 00:24:42,875
The basketball tournament
is the main event.

499
00:24:43,208 --> 00:24:44,708
Our class has to make us proud.

500
00:24:45,458 --> 00:24:46,166
So, sports representative,

501
00:24:46,291 --> 00:24:47,291
get a headcount.

502
00:24:47,375 --> 00:24:48,375
Okay, teacher.

503
00:24:48,750 --> 00:24:49,809
Everyone, please sign up enthusiastically.

504
00:24:49,833 --> 00:24:50,291
I'll sign up.

505
00:24:50,375 --> 00:24:50,791
Zhan Wang.

506
00:24:51,041 --> 00:24:51,750
You have to sign up.

507
00:24:51,958 --> 00:24:53,101
That three-pointer you
made the other day...

508
00:24:53,125 --> 00:24:53,666
we all saw it.

509
00:24:53,833 --> 00:24:54,500
It was a perfect shot.

510
00:24:54,708 --> 00:24:55,208
Yeah, yeah.

511
00:24:55,291 --> 00:24:56,291
You have to sign up.

512
00:24:56,333 --> 00:24:57,166
You have to. Sign up, sign up.

513
00:24:57,166 --> 00:24:57,791
We're counting on you.

514
00:24:58,041 --> 00:24:59,291
Yeah, we can't win without you.

515
00:25:00,083 --> 00:25:01,083
Alright.

516
00:25:01,208 --> 00:25:02,208
But I have one condition.

517
00:25:02,833 --> 00:25:03,208
What is it?

518
00:25:03,708 --> 00:25:04,125
He...

519
00:25:04,666 --> 00:25:05,809
has to be on the team too.

520
00:25:05,833 --> 00:25:06,833
Him?

521
00:25:06,958 --> 00:25:07,958
Him on the team?

522
00:25:08,083 --> 00:25:08,583
Zhan Wang.

523
00:25:08,875 --> 00:25:09,916
You can't be serious.

524
00:25:10,708 --> 00:25:12,500
Basketball is a team sport.

525
00:25:12,750 --> 00:25:13,832
How can we let him on the team?

526
00:25:13,833 --> 00:25:14,833
Zhan Wang.

527
00:25:15,041 --> 00:25:16,761
The sports meet is about our class's honor.

528
00:25:16,791 --> 00:25:18,017
You can't treat this like a joke.

529
00:25:18,041 --> 00:25:18,666
Exactly.

530
00:25:18,916 --> 00:25:19,333
I mean,

531
00:25:19,458 --> 00:25:21,083
what if something happens on the court?

532
00:25:21,291 --> 00:25:22,434
Who's going to be responsible?

533
00:25:22,458 --> 00:25:22,958
Right.

534
00:25:23,333 --> 00:25:25,041
If he gets hurt, whose fault is it?

535
00:25:26,208 --> 00:25:27,208
I won't join.

536
00:25:31,708 --> 00:25:32,948
I'm not suited for team sports.

537
00:25:33,208 --> 00:25:34,267
And I don't like playing basketball.

538
00:25:34,291 --> 00:25:34,833
Oh, that's great.

539
00:25:34,916 --> 00:25:35,458
Then I'll sign up, I'll sign up.

540
00:25:35,458 --> 00:25:36,416
Okay, okay. Anyone else?

541
00:25:36,416 --> 00:25:36,916
You guys sign up.

542
00:25:36,916 --> 00:25:37,916
You're joining with him?

543
00:25:39,708 --> 00:25:41,388
Let's just get the others signed up first.

544
00:25:41,666 --> 00:25:43,506
We'll discuss the
basketball tournament later.

545
00:25:59,583 --> 00:26:00,983
I've been looking all over for you.

546
00:26:03,833 --> 00:26:04,953
How did you know I was here?

547
00:26:06,333 --> 00:26:07,333
Xu Nuo told me.

548
00:26:09,250 --> 00:26:10,610
About the basketball tournament...

549
00:26:11,458 --> 00:26:12,458
don't worry about it.

550
00:26:13,166 --> 00:26:14,458
Those guys are idiots.

551
00:26:14,583 --> 00:26:15,743
They're scared of everything.

552
00:26:16,083 --> 00:26:17,083
They're not wrong.

553
00:26:18,291 --> 00:26:19,531
I'm not suited for team sports.

554
00:26:26,708 --> 00:26:27,708
Xu Yuan.

555
00:26:29,541 --> 00:26:30,791
You can't keep running away.

556
00:26:32,041 --> 00:26:33,761
What right do they have to call you a jinx?

557
00:26:34,458 --> 00:26:35,666
All that talk about curses...

558
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:37,000
it's all nonsense.

559
00:26:37,750 --> 00:26:39,230
They were the ones who had it coming.

560
00:26:43,916 --> 00:26:45,041
You don't know anything.

561
00:26:48,625 --> 00:26:51,166
You don't know what it's like
to watch your own father drown.

562
00:26:52,375 --> 00:26:55,250
You don't know what it's like to see
your only friend get into a car accident.

563
00:26:57,041 --> 00:26:58,267
Every time I try to be good to someone,

564
00:26:58,291 --> 00:26:59,491
something bad happens to them.

565
00:27:00,541 --> 00:27:01,625
Once is a coincidence.

566
00:27:01,666 --> 00:27:02,416
Twice is an accident.

567
00:27:02,500 --> 00:27:03,980
What about the third and fourth time?

568
00:27:07,416 --> 00:27:08,416
You tell me.

569
00:27:09,750 --> 00:27:10,790
Besides accepting my fate,

570
00:27:11,208 --> 00:27:12,250
what else can I do?

571
00:27:15,166 --> 00:27:17,981
I don't know exactly
what happened to you in the past.

572
00:27:19,416 --> 00:27:20,416
But I do know...

573
00:27:21,291 --> 00:27:23,331
what it feels like to
be treated like a monster.

574
00:27:24,916 --> 00:27:25,916
In my family,

575
00:27:26,791 --> 00:27:28,208
my second brother was that monster.

576
00:27:29,791 --> 00:27:31,000
Because he likes men.

577
00:27:39,416 --> 00:27:41,250
In my dad's eyes,
he was a disgrace.

578
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,760
I was also afraid of
becoming a disgrace.

579
00:27:46,750 --> 00:27:48,750
Later, I realized that no
matter how hard I tried,

580
00:27:49,500 --> 00:27:50,791
I could never satisfy him.

581
00:27:52,916 --> 00:27:53,916
So,

582
00:27:54,416 --> 00:27:56,336
there's no difference
between my brother and me.

583
00:27:56,458 --> 00:27:58,298
We're both just useless
embarrassments to him.

584
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:04,000
Xu Yuan.

585
00:28:05,166 --> 00:28:07,046
I'm not trying to compare
sob stories with you.

586
00:28:07,208 --> 00:28:08,208
I just want to say...

587
00:28:10,500 --> 00:28:11,980
that after my grandma passed away,

588
00:28:13,583 --> 00:28:14,583
a lot of things...

589
00:28:15,500 --> 00:28:16,500
became clear to me.

590
00:28:18,916 --> 00:28:19,958
I just want to be me.

591
00:28:20,750 --> 00:28:21,830
And I hope you can be, too.

592
00:28:23,583 --> 00:28:25,541
You were never the jinx
that people see you as.

593
00:28:27,291 --> 00:28:28,291
You...

594
00:28:28,583 --> 00:28:29,583
are just you.

595
00:28:33,416 --> 00:28:34,416
But...

596
00:28:35,041 --> 00:28:36,041
And to me,

597
00:28:36,750 --> 00:28:38,550
you're not the person
who brings me bad luck.

598
00:28:41,708 --> 00:28:43,000
Instead, since I came here,

599
00:28:44,958 --> 00:28:46,598
you're the one who's made me feel warmth.

600
00:28:48,958 --> 00:28:49,958
What if...

601
00:28:50,791 --> 00:28:52,166
I end up hurting you too?

602
00:28:52,750 --> 00:28:54,041
It was never your fault.

603
00:28:55,250 --> 00:28:56,250
Besides,

604
00:28:57,208 --> 00:28:58,291
I'm tough.

605
00:28:59,166 --> 00:29:00,166
I can take a hit.

606
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:04,000
On the basketball court,

607
00:29:05,750 --> 00:29:07,230
you'll be there to protect me, right?

608
00:29:09,291 --> 00:29:10,291
Honestly,

609
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:12,000
that dive you took...

610
00:29:13,166 --> 00:29:14,166
was pretty cool.

611
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:22,000
Alright.

612
00:29:22,291 --> 00:29:23,291
I'll give it a try.

613
00:29:27,791 --> 00:29:29,271
But you have to promise me one thing.

614
00:29:29,916 --> 00:29:30,375
Name it.

615
00:29:30,875 --> 00:29:31,875
Study hard.

616
00:29:32,458 --> 00:29:33,778
And take your homework seriously.

617
00:29:45,875 --> 00:29:46,875
Deal.

618
00:29:58,916 --> 00:29:59,916
Bro.

619
00:30:00,250 --> 00:30:02,583
I can't believe you're
playing basketball again.

620
00:30:03,041 --> 00:30:04,791
Did hell freeze over?

621
00:30:06,250 --> 00:30:07,500
Didn't you say

622
00:30:07,708 --> 00:30:10,083
all sports that require teamwork

623
00:30:10,708 --> 00:30:11,708
were a huge pain?

624
00:30:12,166 --> 00:30:13,875
I'm just dribbling.

625
00:30:14,458 --> 00:30:16,041
It's because Zhan Wang

626
00:30:16,166 --> 00:30:17,646
asked you to join the team, isn't it?

627
00:30:18,791 --> 00:30:21,500
The power of love is a great thing.

628
00:30:22,166 --> 00:30:23,166
Xu Nuo.

629
00:30:23,375 --> 00:30:24,375
See? I was right.

630
00:30:25,041 --> 00:30:25,458
Bro,

631
00:30:25,791 --> 00:30:26,708
you and Zhan Wang

632
00:30:26,709 --> 00:30:28,833
are the talk of Shude High now.

633
00:30:29,500 --> 00:30:31,000
Every move you two make,

634
00:30:31,125 --> 00:30:33,125
nothing gets past me.

635
00:30:36,458 --> 00:30:37,698
Why are you keeping tabs on me?

636
00:30:38,083 --> 00:30:39,250
Just focus on school.

637
00:30:40,333 --> 00:30:42,625
It's just that you've
changed so much lately.

638
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:44,500
I can't help but pay attention.

639
00:30:58,416 --> 00:30:59,000
Zhan Wang.

640
00:30:59,250 --> 00:31:00,392
Are you really putting him in?

641
00:31:00,416 --> 00:31:00,833
Yeah.

642
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:02,000
Why not?

643
00:31:25,791 --> 00:31:26,791
Is he any good?

644
00:31:27,125 --> 00:31:27,541
Yeah.

645
00:31:27,625 --> 00:31:28,625
Can he really play?

646
00:31:28,833 --> 00:31:29,833
Does he even know how?

647
00:31:31,750 --> 00:31:33,309
He's not actually going
for a three-pointer, is he?

648
00:31:33,333 --> 00:31:34,613
There's no way he's making that.

649
00:31:46,500 --> 00:31:48,208
See that? See that?

650
00:31:48,333 --> 00:31:48,916
Incredible!

651
00:31:49,125 --> 00:31:51,245
When it comes to shooting,
none of you can touch him.

652
00:31:51,291 --> 00:31:52,291
I'll say it again.

653
00:31:52,625 --> 00:31:54,166
I'll only join if Xu Yuan joins.

654
00:31:55,083 --> 00:31:56,243
Otherwise, find someone else.

655
00:31:57,500 --> 00:31:58,500
Got it?

